The paper discusses a full-duplex system utilizing Multi-Reconfigurable Antenna (MRA) for self-interference suppression. This involves signal processing, communication theory, and networking, which are all related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also involves system design and optimization (cs.SY), as well as experimental analysis and evaluation (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed system, including natural language processing (cs.CL).
